My brother proceeds to grab sticks and rocks but to no avail....Mike is still getting attacked. Within 3 min about 20 cops showed up weapons drawn, the dogs see the cops and lunge for them, meanwhile my brother and Mike are yelling SHOOT THE FUCKERS, and the cops did just that only killing one and the rest ran off.

Joan told me that she was getting tire a lot now, the coughing is driving her nuts.....she's not sleeping well.  I remember a few months befor my dad had open heart he had a "grey" look upon his skin....I noticed that Joan is getting that same look.  Everytime I go over there I cry all the way home, I don't want her to see me do that, Im trying to stay positive for her with encouraging words and helping any way that I can.

Tears are streaming down my face as I write this, My almost mother in-law just came back from the Oncologist (sp?) and she has stage 4 lung cancer and possible abdominal cancer also. They are sending her for a bone scan and a CT scan at the end of the week.  i am amazed how fast cancer can show its ugly face, she just went for her check-up 2 months ago and there was NO sign of cancer cells to be found.

Im currently reading all that I can find out about stage 4 cancer ....It killed me to see the survival rate for stage 4 cancer....its only 8 months...Im stummed! She hasnt told her kids yet, I asked her if she wanted me to tell her son Phoenyx (he's my ex-fiance) he will handle it better coming from me but she wants to wait till all the tests come back so she can give them all the details.

I can't express how much respect I have for this woman. To see this great woman have to go yet another round with this beast is heart breaking, but I know in my heart she will beat this.

Whelp one hurricane gone another might be on the way.  Went to the beach friday night to checl out the surf and the HOT surfers.Found out the my "almost mother in-law" might have lung cancer this will be round 3 if she does...the 1st was colon cancer...2nd was breast cancer (they removed a breast) , and now this....Im not a "praying" kinda gal but I have done some for her.

I guess Im done.

What was once simple logic is now a bewildering 
maze of altered conditions. 
The more I try to focus, the more blurry things become. 
You get what you ask for but it maybe in a different form. 
Maybe I didn't expect to be here, but there's still time to make the best of it. 
I will do whatever necessary to grab the first fresh moment of the day 
between the cobwebs of my dreams and the stinging memory 
of yesterdays mistakes. 
I've been in my own little world for so long I had forgotten 
what its like to be alone. 
Some offhand remarks carry the weight of official statements. 
I struggle everyday with my shadow self and my evil twin 
in hopes of the right one prevailing 
the bottom line for the most part is that everyone seeks their 
own pleasures and hopes none gets hurt. 
But it doesn't always work that way all the time someone 
gets hurt in the end of it all. 
If I pretend hard and long enough that it doesn't bother me I may 
even convince myself that life is just one big confusing game of give and 
take. Like opponents standing ready to pounce on the first sign of 
weakness, so I wont give them the satisfaction of seeing me squirm. 
The same old thing suddenly feels like a ridiculous waste of time. 
Everyone uses a person as a stepping stone at some point in their life 
only to realize that perfection is only in their state of mind. 
If you have to make a decision based on guesswork, remember you might not get a second chance. 
Some believe that there's a person without substance behind you dazzling 
facade, but soon you'll prove them wrong. 
But why am I still playing the game? 
When I look around, there aren't any other players on the field....are there? 
I think about whether or not there is a reason I haven't noticed that everyone has called a time out. 
Is it possible that I might be in love with the process that no longer serves any real purpose. 
The people around me cant believe how well I seem to know what's going on in their heads, my guesses are so accurate that they make me look like a genie 
I really cant believe he remains my constant companion for yet another 
fun-filled day. 
But I cant quite put my finger on it, something around me has changed 
Something is different in my world ---maybe its me. 
And yet the wild ride continues between us!!
